Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Components", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"90f4bb7a-6e9f-4927-a89f-4031d5b9bf69"],

Cell["\<\
This is a  library of generic associative memory components  and signal flow \
components. Additional components can be plugged in without modification of \
the Circuit code.
Each component defines its callback function, default visualization, and \
static error checks.

Components are generally designed to accept both \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]digital\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] sets and \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]analog\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] multisets. Multisets \
may include inhibitory signals.

By design, circuit components (the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]gray matter\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) are kept as simple as possible. By contrast, the \
signal flow  (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]white matter\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) \
logic offers a broad selection of spatial and temporal routing features. 

Components are generally stateful, while pathways are strictly stateless \
conduits.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7f0793bc-85aa-4b63-b0d8-3c5145431e3d"],

